# UI001 — ui_no_raw_widget_kind
#
# Lint rule: flag string literals passed as the kind argument to WidgetNode.new().
#
# Implementation lives in:
#   src/compiler/90.tools/lint/main.spl — Linter.check_ui_raw_widget_kind()
#
# Rule logic summary:
#   - For each line containing "WidgetNode.new("
#   - Parse the second argument (after first comma inside the call)
#   - If it starts with `"` it is a string literal → emit UI001 warning
#
# Allowlisted paths (never flagged):
#   common/ui/parse/           — SDN/HTML parsers; kind comes from user input
#   common/ui/builder.spl      — top-level builder; legitimate bridge point
#   common/ui/ios/builder.spl  — already uses WidgetKind.X.to_wire()
#   common/ui/glass/builder.spl — already uses WidgetKind.X.to_wire()
#   os/services/llm/widget_eval.spl — runtime eval from LLM user input
#
# Suggested fix: replace "panel" with WidgetKind.Panel.to_wire()
#
# Registration: compiler.tools.lint.main.{all_lint_names, build_default_levels,
#               map_lint_code_to_config_name, Linter.new, Linter.lint_source}
